---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="About — Edward Han" description="About this personal atlas.">
  <section class="grid gap-8 border-b border-black/10 pb-10 pt-6 lg:grid-cols-[1fr_0.9fr]">
    <div>
      <p class="text-[11px] uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-neutral-500">About</p>
      <h1 class="mt-4 max-w-3xl text-4xl font-display leading-tight text-neutral-900 md:text-6xl">
        A small home for work that moves at different speeds.
      </h1>
    </div>
    <div class="space-y-5 text-sm leading-7 text-neutral-600">
      <p>
        This site is being rebuilt as a place where writing and visual travel notes can sit side by side.
        Not a utility-first portfolio, and not only a blog either. More like a personal publication with room for editing, pacing, and return visits.
      </p>
      <p>
        Over time, the travel section can expand from still photographs into short video or vlog posts without needing a new structure.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
